WEBVTT

00:03.469 --> 00:06.003
Welcome back
to "gadget corner."

00:06.004 --> 00:09.273
Next, we have
an air-powered
appliance mover.

00:09.274 --> 00:12.043
This is a very useful device.
I have one of these myself.

00:12.044 --> 00:15.914
It's a way to move furniture
without scratching the floor
or hurting your back.

00:15.915 --> 00:17.615
These panels are attached
to a blower unit.

00:17.616 --> 00:20.052
Right. Marv, close in here.
I'll show you these.

00:20.053 --> 00:22.454
The air is forced into these
aluminum air beams.

00:22.455 --> 00:25.990
Which creates enough air
pressure to lift weights
of up to 700 pounds.

00:25.991 --> 00:29.928
Which is how al moves his mom
room to room.

00:29.929 --> 00:31.863
Can we just...

00:36.201 --> 00:38.403
Can we just
demonstrate this, please?

00:38.404 --> 00:42.374
You just sling the unit
over your shoulder
and turn it on...

00:42.375 --> 00:46.278
And move your refrigerator
effortlessly.

00:46.279 --> 00:48.212
Wow!
Hey!

00:52.051 --> 00:54.018
That is very useful.

00:54.019 --> 00:57.555
You can see how useful this is,
but it only will raise it
about an inch and a quarter.

00:57.556 --> 00:59.690
What happens if you have
to move it up a step?

00:59.691 --> 01:04.296
Well, then you would do it
the old-fashioned way -
by the sweat of your brow.

01:04.297 --> 01:06.297
Let me show you
how I'll do it.

01:06.298 --> 01:09.167
Heidi, my slightly tweaked
furniture mover, please.

01:12.872 --> 01:15.140
Here you go, tim.
Thank you, heidi.

01:15.141 --> 01:17.441
With the few modifications
I've made on this,

01:17.442 --> 01:21.612
I'll now be able
to lift that thing
about a foot and a half.

01:21.613 --> 01:23.948
Help me out here.

01:23.949 --> 01:26.151
All right.
Thank you, heidi.

01:26.152 --> 01:28.419
Just... Oh.

01:28.420 --> 01:31.022
Switch her on.
There you go. Lifts it...

01:31.023 --> 01:32.624
Oh!

01:32.625 --> 01:33.958
Unh!

02:33.452 --> 02:35.486
Hey, brad,
guess what I got.

02:35.487 --> 02:37.789
